cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper deals with declarative networking and distributed computation, which are topics closely related to databases (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of Datalog, a logic programming language, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper presents a hierarchy of classes of coordination-free queries, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS).
